g.text: EOI Timing: Why Forgetting EOI Freezes the System

div.p: Key Point: EOI clears the ISR bit, allowing lower-priority IRQs.
CRITICAL: ISR bit 0 blocks all lower-priority IRQs (IRQ1-IRQ7). System doesn't crashit just stops responding to input!
The PIC won't deliver any IRQ with priority lower than the highest bit set in ISR. IRQ1 (keyboard) has lower priority than IRQ0 (timer).
All ISR bits = 0 All IRQs enabled
